cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks for computer vision tasks such as classification, object detection, and segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the limitations of current attack algorithms and proposes a novel approach based on neural network features, which falls under the scope of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper addresses the security aspect of adversarial attacks, which could potentially fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
